1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,794
[Teresa] <i>Are you sure you're feeling well?</i>

2
00:00:02,877 --> 00:00:03,920
- [pensive music playing]
- Yes, Doctor.

3
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:06,256
[Teresa] <i>Just don't push</i>
<i>yourself too hard.</i>

4
00:00:06,339 --> 00:00:08,049
<i>Jamilah, I don't know why,</i>

5
00:00:08,133 --> 00:00:12,345
<i>but I think Allan is Gabriel,</i>
<i>my missing son.</i>

6
00:00:12,429 --> 00:00:14,014
How could that be?

7
00:00:14,097 --> 00:00:15,849
I feel bound to him.

8
00:00:15,932 --> 00:00:18,143
[Teresa] <i>Maybe I'm going crazy,</i>

9
00:00:18,226 --> 00:00:22,355
<i>but I have this feeling</i>
<i>that my son is still alive.</i>

10
00:00:22,439 --> 00:00:24,441
<i>I have to try.</i>

11
00:00:25,191 --> 00:00:26,693
<i>I need an answer.</i>

12
00:00:28,486 --> 00:00:29,904
[Marcus] <i>They used the kid</i>
<i>to blackmail them,</i>

13
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:31,781
<i>so they would be forced to hijack the bus.</i>

14
00:00:31,865 --> 00:00:34,743
<i>From the start, they were never</i>
<i>going to make it out alive.</i>

15
00:00:34,826 --> 00:00:40,081
[Azuelo] <i>We need to put a stop</i>
<i>to all of General Carillo's evil schemes!</i>

16
00:00:40,165 --> 00:00:43,168
Mustapha and General Carillo
will face each other.

17
00:00:43,251 --> 00:00:45,003
That's your chance.

18
00:00:45,086 --> 00:00:46,671
Once it passes,

19
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:50,508
they're bound to carry out
their wicked plans.

20
00:00:51,468 --> 00:00:52,719
What are you doing here?

21
00:00:52,802 --> 00:00:55,388
Lara hasn't reported
to the headquarters for several days.

22
00:00:55,472 --> 00:00:56,514
[Marcus] <i>Buster mentioned</i>

23
00:00:56,598 --> 00:00:59,601
<i>that Lara suddenly disappeared</i>
<i>after the explosion.</i>

24
00:00:59,684 --> 00:01:00,685
<i>No one can find her.</i>

25
00:01:00,769 --> 00:01:03,021
Did you have an opportunity
to speak with Lara

26
00:01:03,104 --> 00:01:05,356
before or after the explosion?

27
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:06,608
[Manuel] <i>Tell me the truth.</i>

28
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:08,109
<i>Was it you who activated the detonator?</i>

29
00:01:08,193 --> 00:01:09,527
[Felix, in English] <i>Yes, General.</i>

30
00:01:09,611 --> 00:01:12,238
- [screaming]
- [glass breaks]

31
00:01:13,114 --> 00:01:15,617
[Felix] <i>Don't you dare mess up, Lara.</i>

32
00:01:16,326 --> 00:01:17,911
I don't want to kill you.

33
00:01:18,661 --> 00:01:20,830
[Felix] <i>I don't want to kill you, Lara.</i>

34
00:01:23,124 --> 00:01:29,881
[mysterious theme music playing]

35
00:01:40,183 --> 00:01:46,439
[suspenseful music playing]

36
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:08,563
‪[door squeaks]

37
00:03:12,358 --> 00:03:13,192
‪[door squeaks]

38
00:03:34,839 --> 00:03:35,965
[choking]

39
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:36,883
Who are you?!

40
00:03:36,966 --> 00:03:38,760
[Datu Rahman stammering]

41
00:03:38,843 --> 00:03:40,345
Why are you here?!

42
00:03:40,428 --> 00:03:41,846
[groans]

43
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:45,183
[music intensifies]

44
00:03:45,850 --> 00:03:46,976
Who are you?

45
00:03:47,810 --> 00:03:49,062
Why are you doing this?

46
00:03:49,145 --> 00:03:50,813
[coughing, grunting]

47
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:52,899
Why am I doing this, huh?

48
00:03:52,982 --> 00:03:54,692
- You dare ask me that question?!
- [grunts]

49
00:03:54,776 --> 00:03:56,611
Because you killed my parents, that's why!

50
00:03:56,694 --> 00:03:59,239
I don't understand
what you're talking about!

51
00:03:59,864 --> 00:04:02,325
What? You don't remember?

52
00:04:03,034 --> 00:04:03,952
There!

53
00:04:04,035 --> 00:04:05,411
[suspenseful music playing]

54
00:04:05,495 --> 00:04:07,830
You still don't remember, huh?

55
00:04:07,914 --> 00:04:09,499
[in English] 1997!

56
00:04:09,582 --> 00:04:11,167
[in English] Cabatangon Medical Mission!

57
00:04:11,251 --> 00:04:12,919
You killed my parents!

58
00:04:13,002 --> 00:04:15,296
You killed a lot of innocent people!

59
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:16,589
I saw you with my own eyes!

60
00:04:16,673 --> 00:04:19,968
I saw how you killed my parents!

61
00:04:20,051 --> 00:04:25,223
- [dramatic sting]
- [music intensifies]

62
00:04:25,306 --> 00:04:26,140
‪[dramatic sting]

63
00:04:28,142 --> 00:04:28,977
‪[dramatic sting]

64
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:30,186
It was you?

65
00:04:31,729 --> 00:04:33,064
You were the little girl?

66
00:04:34,148 --> 00:04:35,650
- [Jamilah] Father?!
- [gasps] Jamilah!

67
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:37,068
[Jamilah] Father!

68
00:04:37,151 --> 00:04:38,069
- [Jamilah] Father!
- I'm warning you!

69
00:04:38,152 --> 00:04:39,445
- I dare you--
- Don't hurt my father!

70
00:04:39,529 --> 00:04:40,405
Shut up!

71
00:04:40,488 --> 00:04:42,407
Take one more step, and he dies!

72
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:45,535
- Father! [gasps]
- [Datu Rahman] Jamilah…

73
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:48,705
- Stay right there, Jamilah.
- Don't you dare hurt him!

74
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:50,832
Jamilah, stay where you are.
Don't move closer!

75
00:04:50,915 --> 00:04:52,834
- [Jamilah breathing heavily]
- [in English] I have nothing to lose.

76
00:04:52,917 --> 00:04:54,627
I don't care if they kill me out there.

77
00:04:56,838 --> 00:04:59,924
I came here because I'm going
to avenge my parents.

78
00:05:01,759 --> 00:05:03,428
You killed my parents.

79
00:05:03,511 --> 00:05:05,471
You ruined my entire life!

80
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:10,143
I did not kill your parents. Believe me.

81
00:05:10,226 --> 00:05:11,894
- I did not kill them--
- It was you!

82
00:05:11,978 --> 00:05:14,022
You're a liar! You're a liar!

83
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:15,857
I'm telling the truth.

84
00:05:15,940 --> 00:05:17,358
[chuckles wryly]

85
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:21,362
It was all Colonel Marcelino's plan.

86
00:05:21,946 --> 00:05:23,323
He tricked us.

87
00:05:24,073 --> 00:05:25,241
No… N-No.

88
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:29,662
He ordered the attack
on the medical mission.

89
00:05:31,039 --> 00:05:35,710
He recruited us,
in the hopes of building a new nation.

90
00:05:36,419 --> 00:05:38,713
We stirred chaos in different towns.

91
00:05:39,213 --> 00:05:40,465
- [Jamilah breathing heavily]
- [music fades]

92
00:05:40,548 --> 00:05:43,468
We spread illegal weapons for them.

93
00:05:44,052 --> 00:05:45,303
He deceived us.

94
00:05:45,386 --> 00:05:47,555
- No… No! [whimpers]
- [somber music playing]

95
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:51,309
It's a lie when he says
it was for a good cause.

96
00:05:51,392 --> 00:05:52,560
No!

97
00:05:52,643 --> 00:05:55,980
[Datu Rahman] He used us
just to make money.

98
00:05:56,814 --> 00:05:59,776
And because he was greedy for power,

99
00:06:00,443 --> 00:06:05,573
he turned us into fake revolutionaries,
into criminals!

100
00:06:05,656 --> 00:06:08,659
- [Datu Rahman whimpers]
- [Lara sobs]

101
00:06:08,743 --> 00:06:10,578
When I found out about their plan

102
00:06:10,661 --> 00:06:14,624
to attack the medical mission
in Barangay Cabatangon,

103
00:06:14,707 --> 00:06:17,043
I went there to stop them.

104
00:06:17,126 --> 00:06:18,628
- But I couldn't do anything.
- No.

105
00:06:18,711 --> 00:06:20,838
It was too late when I arrived.

106
00:06:23,341 --> 00:06:25,510
[young Lara] What did you do?!

107
00:06:25,593 --> 00:06:28,554
You saw me back then
approaching your parents

108
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:30,264
to check their pulse.

109
00:06:30,348 --> 00:06:33,184
- [Datu Rahman] But they were already dead.
- No… No!

110
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:35,645
[Datu Rahman] What I found there

111
00:06:36,354 --> 00:06:38,439
were bloodied corpses

112
00:06:38,523 --> 00:06:41,234
- [Lara sobs]
- and grieving families.

113
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:44,028
[crying]

114
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:46,864
[Lara sniffles]

115
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:51,035
- [cries, sobs]
- [Datu Rahman] That's when I decided…

116
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:52,995
[Lara sobs]

117
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:55,373
…to leave their group.

118
00:06:55,456 --> 00:06:57,625
[breathing heavily]

119
00:06:57,708 --> 00:07:01,170
I hid on Damai Island.

120
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:04,465
I changed my name
so they couldn't find me,

121
00:07:05,216 --> 00:07:07,260
and so I could start over.

122
00:07:07,343 --> 00:07:10,346
[breathing heavily]

123
00:07:11,347 --> 00:07:12,682
I have…

124
00:07:12,765 --> 00:07:17,019
[whimpers] I have committed
many sins in my life.

125
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:19,647
[sobbing]

126
00:07:19,730 --> 00:07:23,901
But killing your parents
is not one of them.

127
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:26,654
[somber music playing]

128
00:07:26,737 --> 00:07:29,115
- [Jamilah breathes heavily]
- [knife clatters]

129
00:07:30,324 --> 00:07:31,701
[gasps]

130
00:07:31,784 --> 00:07:33,244
[Jamilah breathing heavily]

131
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:34,162
‪[breathing heavily]

132
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:41,294
[breathing heavily]

133
00:07:41,377 --> 00:07:44,046
[whimpering]

134
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:45,381
Jamilah…

135
00:07:48,259 --> 00:07:49,469
Jamilah, my dear.

136
00:07:49,552 --> 00:07:54,640
- N-No… [whimpering, breathing heavily]
- Jamilah…

137
00:07:59,061 --> 00:08:01,397
[sobs]

138
00:08:02,773 --> 00:08:06,736
[breathing heavily]

139
00:08:08,404 --> 00:08:09,489
[exhales deeply]

140
00:08:09,572 --> 00:08:12,492
[screaming]

141
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:22,835
[crying]

142
00:08:22,919 --> 00:08:28,049
[screaming]

143
00:08:28,132 --> 00:08:31,052
[sobbing]

144
00:08:31,135 --> 00:08:35,097
[screaming, sobbing]

145
00:08:44,232 --> 00:08:45,942
- [pensive music playing]
- [breathes heavily] Father…

146
00:08:47,026 --> 00:08:48,653
Who is that woman?

147
00:08:49,445 --> 00:08:51,822
Isn't she a member of Task Force Alpha?

148
00:08:51,906 --> 00:08:54,784
- What was she talking about?
- [Datu Rahman] Jamilah…

149
00:08:55,576 --> 00:08:57,954
- [sobs] Is it true?!
- Dear, sit down.

150
00:08:58,037 --> 00:08:59,539
- [chair slides]
- Sit down first.

151
00:08:59,622 --> 00:09:00,831
Sit down.

152
00:09:01,582 --> 00:09:02,667
[sobs]

153
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,418
I have something to tell you.

154
00:09:04,502 --> 00:09:08,130
[breathing heavily]

155
00:09:11,092 --> 00:09:14,804
Rahman is not my real name.

156
00:09:17,723 --> 00:09:19,767
My real name is Hassan Wadi.

157
00:09:22,728 --> 00:09:27,608
I changed my name to escape
Colonel Marcelino's group.

158
00:09:27,692 --> 00:09:30,695
[breathes heavily]
And you were saying earlier, Father…

159
00:09:32,113 --> 00:09:37,368
that you really were connected
to the syndicates

160
00:09:37,868 --> 00:09:40,496
dealing with illegal firearms?

161
00:09:41,664 --> 00:09:43,583
That was before, my dear.

162
00:09:44,709 --> 00:09:48,004
I left that life a long time ago.

163
00:09:49,338 --> 00:09:52,258
Ever since I adopted Jalil,

164
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:57,763
I've decided to live peacefully.

165
00:09:58,472 --> 00:10:00,725
[breathes heavily]

166
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:05,521
But it seems your past
is always out to haunt you…

167
00:10:07,565 --> 00:10:11,652
because of what I did to hide the weapons

168
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:15,323
that were being brought around our island.

169
00:10:16,824 --> 00:10:18,701
Is that how they tracked you?

170
00:10:21,245 --> 00:10:24,206
Is that why they targeted our island?

171
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:26,459
[Datu Rahman breathing rapidly]

172
00:10:26,542 --> 00:10:30,546
All I ever wanted
is to protect our island.

173
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:31,714
[breathing heavily]

174
00:10:31,797 --> 00:10:35,635
I didn't expect everything
to turn out this way.

175
00:10:38,387 --> 00:10:40,431
Please forgive me, Jamilah.

176
00:10:41,015 --> 00:10:44,935
I didn't tell the whole truth
to you and Jalil.

177
00:10:46,562 --> 00:10:49,065
I was scared. I was…

178
00:10:49,148 --> 00:10:51,359
I was ashamed.

179
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:59,492
Because, although their accusations
against me now are not true,

180
00:11:00,701 --> 00:11:03,913
the blood of our neighbors
who died that night

181
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:09,251
are still on my hands.

182
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:12,088
[Jamilah breathes heavily]

183
00:11:13,464 --> 00:11:15,424
[Datu Rahman sniffles, exhales]

184
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:18,135
I'm begging you, my dear.

185
00:11:19,428 --> 00:11:23,432
Let me be the one to tell Jalil all this.

186
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:25,893
[Jamilah breathing shakily]

187
00:11:25,976 --> 00:11:27,520
[chair scraping]

188
00:11:30,689 --> 00:11:31,524
[cries softly]

189
00:11:32,358 --> 00:11:36,570
[Datu Rahman exhales]

190
00:11:39,448 --> 00:11:41,784
Promise me, Father.

191
00:11:43,411 --> 00:11:46,705
You will tell the truth to Jalil.

192
00:11:48,165 --> 00:11:49,917
Maybe not now,

193
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:53,546
but I hope, Father, that you find a chance

194
00:11:54,713 --> 00:11:57,299
to tell him the truth.

195
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:02,221
I promise, Jamilah. I promise.

196
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:06,684
[Jamilah breathes shakily]

197
00:12:08,936 --> 00:12:10,187
[Jamilah sniffles]

198
00:12:11,313 --> 00:12:14,108
Sir, we're trying to find out
what happened to Lara.

199
00:12:14,191 --> 00:12:16,569
- [pensive music playing]
- However, as of now, we have no news.

200
00:12:16,652 --> 00:12:17,945
And Manuel?

201
00:12:18,028 --> 00:12:19,363
He also doesn't know where she is?

202
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:22,116
That's what Marcus observed.

203
00:12:29,457 --> 00:12:32,626
Was there something that triggered her to…

204
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:34,336
just disappear like that?

205
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:37,423
I think it was the explosion.

206
00:12:39,383 --> 00:12:41,218
Sir, I also found out that

207
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:44,638
Lara's parents died
during a medical mission.

208
00:12:45,514 --> 00:12:46,891
They were ambushed.

209
00:12:47,683 --> 00:12:49,143
She was orphaned,

210
00:12:50,311 --> 00:12:52,646
then General Carillo took her in.

211
00:12:52,730 --> 00:12:56,025
But I'm not sure if it's in any way
related to all of this.

212
00:12:57,318 --> 00:12:58,944
- [gunshot]
- [people clamoring]

213
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:01,489
Just like what happened
during a medical mission

214
00:13:01,572 --> 00:13:02,531
- <i>in Mindanao.</i>
- [young Lara crying]

215
00:13:03,324 --> 00:13:05,493
[Datu Rahman] <i>He's the one</i>
<i>who started the chaos.</i>

216
00:13:05,576 --> 00:13:08,245
But it is the Muslim rebels
who took the fall for it.

217
00:13:09,246 --> 00:13:12,124
I tried to stop him,
but I couldn't do anything.

218
00:13:14,043 --> 00:13:16,629
Lara…

219
00:13:17,379 --> 00:13:22,384
is the weakest link in Carillo's group.

220
00:13:24,053 --> 00:13:26,347
She's the most vulnerable.

221
00:13:26,847 --> 00:13:28,557
You need to find her.

222
00:13:29,058 --> 00:13:31,852
Because if my hunch is right,

223
00:13:33,395 --> 00:13:35,606
her life is in danger.

224
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:39,944
And it's because
of her adoptive father himself.

225
00:13:41,195 --> 00:13:47,159
[pensive music playing]

226
00:13:47,243 --> 00:13:48,994
[suspenseful sting]

227
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:54,041
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

228
00:13:54,124 --> 00:13:57,002
COL. LUIS DEL MUNDO FOUND DEAD

229
00:14:02,883 --> 00:14:04,843
[suspenseful sting]

230
00:14:05,553 --> 00:14:06,971
♪ <i>Opening my eyes after a blink</i> ♪

231
00:14:07,054 --> 00:14:09,932
What is going on with you, Agent Angeles?

232
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:15,396
♪ <i>The throne a tyrant playing king ♪</i>

233
00:14:15,479 --> 00:14:17,773
[Marcus] <i>Why did you suddenly</i>
<i>disappear, Lara?</i>

234
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:27,074
<i>Were you the one who blew the bus up?</i>

235
00:14:27,658 --> 00:14:30,286
Is Sir Mustapha telling the truth?

236
00:14:31,495 --> 00:14:33,497
Is your life really in danger?

237
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:35,749
You need to find her.

238
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:38,878
Because if my hunch is right,

239
00:14:38,961 --> 00:14:40,504
her life is in danger.

240
00:14:40,588 --> 00:14:41,255
DATU RAHMAN'S ARREST LED TO A MASSACRE

241
00:14:42,172 --> 00:14:44,049
[Marcus] <i>I hope my hunch is wrong.</i>

242
00:14:47,928 --> 00:14:52,600
Can your own adoptive father kill you?

243
00:14:54,351 --> 00:14:56,687
♪ <i>My enemy over there</i> ♪

244
00:14:56,770 --> 00:15:01,066
♪ <i>A rotten system</i>
<i>Where straight gets twisted</i> ♪

245
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:08,282
♪ <i>Can’t go along with it</i>
<i>Even if it costs me my life</i> ♪

246
00:15:08,365 --> 00:15:11,493
♪ <i>If the law is only for a select few</i> ♪

247
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:13,287
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio ends]

248
00:15:13,370 --> 00:15:15,789
[Datu Rahman] <i>Please forgive me, Jamilah.</i>

249
00:15:15,873 --> 00:15:20,002
<i>I didn't tell the whole truth</i>
<i>to you and Jalil.</i>

250
00:15:20,502 --> 00:15:23,714
[inhales] <i>I was scared. I was…</i>

251
00:15:24,214 --> 00:15:26,216
<i>I was ashamed.</i>

252
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:29,553
- [sighs]
- <i>Because, although their accusations</i>

253
00:15:29,637 --> 00:15:32,473
<i>against me now are not true,</i>

254
00:15:33,766 --> 00:15:36,769
<i>the blood of our neighbors</i>
<i>who died that night</i>

255
00:15:38,145 --> 00:15:42,441
<i>are still on my hands.</i>

256
00:15:43,776 --> 00:15:46,904
[Jamilah] <i>I want to tell you</i>
<i>everything, Jalil.</i>

257
00:15:47,404 --> 00:15:50,074
<i>But I'll leave it to Father to do that.</i>

258
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:53,702
<i>You need to hear the truth from him.</i>

259
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:59,166
[somber music playing]

260
00:16:08,592 --> 00:16:10,135
[sighs]

261
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:16,600
[clicks tongue]

262
00:16:16,684 --> 00:16:22,856
[deep breath]

263
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:24,191
Lara, where are you?

264
00:16:27,027 --> 00:16:29,822
Where are you? God… [sniffles]

265
00:16:32,116 --> 00:16:34,618
[breathes deeply]

266
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:38,706
I hope I'm wrong.

267
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:41,291
[inhales]

268
00:16:41,792 --> 00:16:44,169
I hope my hunch is wrong.

269
00:16:46,839 --> 00:16:49,883
[sniffles]

270
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:55,889
I hope I'm wrong.

271
00:16:55,973 --> 00:16:57,224
[sniffles]

272
00:16:58,267 --> 00:16:59,268
[clicks tongue]

273
00:17:01,145 --> 00:17:01,979
[Lara] <i>Is it true, Uncle?</i>

274
00:17:02,062 --> 00:17:03,856
- [tense music playing]
- [Lara sighs]

275
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:06,108
Was Colonel Napoleon my dad's brother?

276
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:08,986
Is he the reason why my friends died?

277
00:17:09,069 --> 00:17:10,946
Is that true?! [breathes heavily]

278
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:13,449
Tell me the truth! [breathes heavily]

279
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:15,743
Calm down, Lara.

280
00:17:15,826 --> 00:17:17,161
[Lara scoffs]

281
00:17:17,244 --> 00:17:19,288
You don't have to point a gun at me.

282
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:21,290
Believe me.

283
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:22,958
Right now,

284
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:25,711
I'm the only ally you've got left.

285
00:17:25,794 --> 00:17:28,338
Answer my question! Is it true?!

286
00:17:29,131 --> 00:17:31,175
[tense music playing]

287
00:17:31,258 --> 00:17:33,635
Napoleon was a good friend of mine.

288
00:17:34,762 --> 00:17:38,348
I was one of the first recruits
in his organization

289
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:41,810
that aimed to build a new Philippines.

290
00:17:43,353 --> 00:17:45,272
Everything was going fine back then.

291
00:17:46,356 --> 00:17:48,192
He had direction,

292
00:17:48,776 --> 00:17:50,402
he had principles,

293
00:17:50,903 --> 00:17:54,823
but over time,
his brother became aggressive.

294
00:17:56,700 --> 00:17:58,577
Manuel was unpredictable.

295
00:18:00,245 --> 00:18:03,874
Even Napoleon couldn't control him.

296
00:18:04,541 --> 00:18:08,087
He didn't care who he clashed with.

297
00:18:09,129 --> 00:18:13,759
To him, everyone else
was just collateral damage

298
00:18:14,551 --> 00:18:16,261
to achieve a greater goal.

299
00:18:16,345 --> 00:18:18,472
- [dramatic sting]
- [music intensifies]

300
00:18:18,555 --> 00:18:23,477
He did some things
without Napoleon's go signal,

301
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:26,146
yet Manuel brandished his name on it.

302
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:29,775
[breathes deeply]

303
00:18:30,275 --> 00:18:31,735
What did Dad do?

304
00:18:32,361 --> 00:18:35,364
He conducted a lot
of operations on his own.

305
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:37,783
[tense sinister music playing]

306
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:45,040
He blew up a ship that was carrying
a lot of weapons.

307
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:46,708
[sobs]

308
00:18:46,792 --> 00:18:51,255
That was to hide our operation
from the police.

309
00:18:55,801 --> 00:18:57,511
But before that,

310
00:18:57,594 --> 00:19:01,515
- he headed another attack.
- [Lara whimpers]

311
00:19:01,598 --> 00:19:03,642
- It was back in 1997.
- [Lara gasps]

312
00:19:03,725 --> 00:19:09,481
- [dramatic sting]
- [music intensifies]

313
00:19:10,983 --> 00:19:12,526
The medical mission.

314
00:19:13,819 --> 00:19:16,488
- [scoffs]
- [Dante sighs]

315
00:19:21,577 --> 00:19:25,289
It was Manuel
who killed your parents, Lara.

316
00:19:25,873 --> 00:19:27,374
[crying]

317
00:19:27,457 --> 00:19:31,253
He was the mastermind behind that attack.

318
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:34,590
He wanted to frame the Muslim rebels.

319
00:19:34,673 --> 00:19:37,092
[crying]

320
00:19:37,176 --> 00:19:41,889
Just like that bus
he blew up the other day.

321
00:19:42,389 --> 00:19:45,893
He was framing
the communists up with that one.

322
00:19:45,976 --> 00:19:48,061
[sobbing]

323
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:51,940
I'm telling you this

324
00:19:53,525 --> 00:19:56,904
because I have a hunch…

325
00:19:59,489 --> 00:20:04,328
that Manuel killed his own brother,

326
00:20:05,287 --> 00:20:08,248
so nobody would get
in the way of his plans.

327
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:13,086
That's what he always does.

328
00:20:13,170 --> 00:20:15,923
He eliminates anyone who gets in his way.

329
00:20:16,006 --> 00:20:21,511
[dramatic sting]

330
00:20:22,262 --> 00:20:23,680
Listen to me, dear.

331
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:26,808
Be very careful.

332
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:32,606
[music intensifies]

333
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:56,296
- [explosion]
- [people screaming]

334
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:57,923
[young Lara] <i>Mommy!</i>

335
00:20:58,465 --> 00:20:59,967
<i>Mommy! Daddy!</i>

336
00:21:00,050 --> 00:21:01,593
<i>Mommy!</i>

337
00:21:01,677 --> 00:21:05,931
[morose music playing]

338
00:21:06,014 --> 00:21:09,977
[Lara] <i>We're hurting a lot of people,</i>
<i>including kids.</i>

339
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:11,353
[Lara sobs]

340
00:21:22,531 --> 00:21:25,659
I did not kill your parents!

341
00:21:25,742 --> 00:21:27,744
Believe me! I didn't kill them!

342
00:21:27,828 --> 00:21:30,455
You're a liar! You're a liar!

343
00:21:30,539 --> 00:21:33,208
It was all Colonel Marcelino's plan.

344
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:34,793
It was his command!

345
00:21:34,876 --> 00:21:37,379
He was behind the attack
on the medical mission.

346
00:21:39,006 --> 00:21:42,134
It was Manuel who killed
your parents, Lara.

347
00:21:43,343 --> 00:21:47,139
He was the mastermind behind that attack.

348
00:21:47,222 --> 00:21:49,266
He wanted to frame the Muslim rebels.

349
00:21:49,349 --> 00:21:50,767
[sobs]

350
00:21:50,851 --> 00:21:52,894
I'm telling you this

351
00:21:52,978 --> 00:21:56,106
because I have a hunch…

352
00:21:56,773 --> 00:22:00,694
that Manuel killed his own brother,

353
00:22:00,777 --> 00:22:03,155
so nobody would get
in the way of his plans.

354
00:22:03,822 --> 00:22:05,949
That's what he always does.

355
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:09,161
He eliminates anyone who gets in his way.

356
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:11,455
[Dante] <i>Listen to me, dear.</i>

357
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:14,791
<i>Be very careful.</i>

358
00:22:17,169 --> 00:22:18,879
[gun clicks]

359
00:22:18,962 --> 00:22:20,380
[suspenseful music playing]

360
00:22:20,464 --> 00:22:21,548
[breathes heavily]

361
00:22:21,631 --> 00:22:24,551
[Lara] <i>You've kept</i>
<i>so many secrets from me, Dad.</i>

362
00:22:25,886 --> 00:22:28,889
[sobs] <i>I'll make you pay.</i>

363
00:22:31,475 --> 00:22:38,440
[music intensifies]

364
00:22:41,401 --> 00:22:45,238
Please welcome two
of the most important personalities

365
00:22:45,322 --> 00:22:47,574
- in matters of national security.
- [tense music playing]

366
00:22:48,408 --> 00:22:54,206
This all started
after an explosion aboard M/V Doña Emilia.

367
00:22:55,248 --> 00:22:57,959
Sir, do you really believe
that it wasn't an accident?

368
00:22:58,043 --> 00:22:59,544
Why do you ask?

369
00:22:59,628 --> 00:23:01,254
My brother died in that tragedy.

370
00:23:01,922 --> 00:23:05,383
[Teresa] They were the ones who caused
the tragedy where Gabriel died.

371
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:10,180
I've been mourning the loss
of my son for so long, Jamilah.

372
00:23:10,263 --> 00:23:13,517
I'll tell him the truth, Omar,
even if it's hard.

373
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:14,935
How's Father doing?

374
00:23:15,018 --> 00:23:16,394
You have a lot to talk about.

375
00:23:16,478 --> 00:23:20,690
We need to keep a close eye
on Felix from now on.

376
00:23:20,774 --> 00:23:24,611
[Espina] We don't know who among
our comrades we can really trust.

377
00:23:24,694 --> 00:23:25,529
[man grunts]

378
00:23:27,155 --> 00:23:28,615
[Lara] <i>You've been</i>
<i>lying to me for so long!</i>

379
00:23:28,698 --> 00:23:32,244
[in English] I put you on the right side
of history, beside me!

380
00:23:32,327 --> 00:23:33,787
- No!
- [Felix] Lara!

381
00:23:36,373 --> 00:23:37,207
[Felix] <i>I'll avenge you.</i>

382
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:39,835
[screams]

383
00:23:39,918 --> 00:23:42,170
- [Ahmad] <i>I think we'll have to fight.</i>
- [upbeat song playing]

384
00:23:42,254 --> 00:23:47,050
♪ <i>I refuse to be used anymore</i>
<i>Enough is enough</i> ♪

385
00:23:47,134 --> 00:23:50,011
♪ <i>I will fight, I will take a stand</i> ♪

386
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:53,890
♪ <i>If the law is only for a select few</i> ♪
